    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>, java.util.SortedSet<E>, OperatingSet<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SortedTreeModel.TNode

    public class SortedArraySet<E>
extends ArraySet<E>
implements java.util.SortedSet<E>
    SortedArraySet is an extension of ArraySet implementing the SortedSet interface. All elements inserted into this set must implement the Comparable interface or be accepted by the specified comparator. A sorted set has advantage when a single set is used iteratively with dominating membership requests or set operations (OperatingSet), for their execution time.

    Methods of the SortedSet interface which render views of a set as subsets are currently not supported.

    Complexities (of the implementation of this class):
    Single item: insertion, removal and iteration cost O(n), membership O(log n) execution time, n = size(). Set operations (s1, s2) (OperatingSet) cost O(n+m) with n=|s1|, m=|s2|.
